You need to convert string into number first before using `Number.isInteger`.

[`Number.isInteger`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/isInteger) will always return false if the given argument is not typeof number.

Values retrieved from the DOM is always typeof string.

You can convert string into integer using [`parseInt`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/parseInt).

